Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.08,0:22:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,基础设施团队的角色就是支持任何需要帮助的团队\Ninfrastructure's role was to support any team that needed help
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.22,0:23:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,我们的KPI就是其他团队认可我们的帮助\Nand do it in a way that you know your key indicators of success are going to be other teams saying yeah that really helped us
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.92,0:23:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,咨询Tom他们就像咨询元老院一样，他们会给出建议\Nyou go to them and you kind of consult the Council of Elders and they they give you their recommendation and I
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.22,0:23:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,我问道，我们现在要做CSR，你们有什么建议吗？\Nsaid hey we need to do client rendering what do we do and the recommendation at
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.90,0:23:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,他们说我们也不知道，我们现在有三个CSR选项，也许你应该尝试其中一个\Nthe time was yeah we don't know we've got like three different things that we're working on you should go try one
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.41,0:23:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,三个选项如下，一个是Bolt，一个是jshtml\Nwe had uh something called bolt Js there was a second thing called jshtml
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.53,0:23:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,还有就是一个叫React的东西\Nand then there was this this thing called react
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.98,0:23:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Pete跟Jordan讨论了使用React，和我讨论了使用Bolt，但是我觉得他非常喜欢React的函数式思想\Nyou wouldn't spoke to Jordan about using react and he came and talked to me about potentially using both for it but I think he really really liked Jordan's ideas around functional programming
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.86,0:23:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,React的核心概念具有非同一般的创造性，和我的内心共鸣\Nthe conceptual model of react was like crazy Innovative and it really really spoke to me
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.20,0:24:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,我并不喜欢前端，也不看好前端当时的发展\Nmy background was in distributed systems I was not somebody that loved front end or thought front end was like doing things well
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.60,0:24:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,所以我并不在乎此前前端的最佳实践，所以对带着全新开发范式出现的React接受很快，\Nso the fact that react came in with like a totally Fresh Approach and like didn't really care too much about existing best practices like I was I was on board with that so while
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.03,0:24:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,我衡量了三个选项以后选中了React，用它写了Instagram网站的原型，成了最终发布版本的基础\NI had evaluated all three I really just dove in on react to build a prototype first and that ended up shipping on instagram.com
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.68,0:24:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,这是有史以来React在生产环境的第二次应用，是第一次用React构造端到端整个应用\Nwhich was the second use of of reactant production ever and the first use of building a full application end to end in react
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.78,0:24:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,那时即使在Facebook内部React也是不为人知的，它像是一个秘密的疯狂科学试验\Nwhen I chose react for Instagram it was not well known within Facebook and it was this like kind of crazy science experiment
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.34,0:24:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,[对于应用到Instagram网站，当时的React准备好了吗？]
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.88,0:24:41.14,Default,,0,0,0,,还差得很远\Nnot even close
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.14,0:24:45.66,Default,,0,0,0,,在Pete开始将React用于Instagram的时候\Nby the time Instagram was and you know Pete was started playing with it
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.92,0:24:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,React已经比之前好太多，但是依然处于早期发展阶段，还需很多迭代改善\Nuh it was significantly better than it was in the early early stage uh but it still needed a ton of iteration
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.08,0:24:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,当时的React和Facebook的基础设施耦合在一起\Nwe had to take this thing that was very much tied to Facebook's infrastructure
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.26,0:25:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,所谓的基础设施就是一个巨大的PHP应用\Nwhich back then was a big giant PHP application and I had to go get that
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.41,0:25:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,我需要将React和Facebook解耦，然后让它配合Instagram的后端django应用\Nworking in a Django application which is a totally different system and what was
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.88,0:25:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,这项工作的窍门是不要想一次完成工作，而是让迁移可持续，并且确保迁移的管道正常运转\Nkey was not doing that once but making that a repeatable process and and making sure that that pipeline didn't break
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.72,0:25:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我记得Pete遇到了很多有趣的问题，说明了React还不能拿来做Instagram规模的应用\NI think he hit a number of really interesting problems along the way which quite proved the fact that react was not quite ready for that scale
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.16,0:25:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,为了解决问题，Pete和他的团队也在这个过程中构建了很多有意思的东西\Nand along the way Pete and the team that he was working with into that building a lot of really interesting things
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.58,0:25:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,[Music]
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.08,0:25:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,foreign
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.34,0:25:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,早期使用React的几个项目都相当成功\Nsome of these products ended up being fairly successful there were relatively
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.08,0:26:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,它们都在较短的开发时间内达成了较高的质量，证明了React是一种有效的开发方式\Nshort time to to deliver a relatively high quality product that show that this model could work
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.90,0:26:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,不仅如此，人们开始喜欢使用它，这让React逐渐扩散和起飞\Nand it was not just that but people liked developing using it and so that kind of spread and took off
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.42,0:26:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,特别是使用越来越多以后，人们意识到这是他们喜欢的开发方式\Nand especially if you got more and more investment they came clear that this was what we wanted to use and
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.56,0:26:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,但当时广告团队已经在重度使用Bolt，很多人对Bolt已经非常熟悉，对于他们来说迁移到React的成本会更高\Nit was really ads that was kind of using Baltimore it had a higher level investment more people working in that code base that already knew it and more components so it was a harder shift to make
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.76,0:26:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,广告团队在我加入之前刚刚用Bolt重写了"广告创建流"模块，花了他们六个月用Bolt代替古老的PHP代码\Nthe ads team just before I joined ads from the mobile team had done a full rewrite of the ads creation flow into bolt which took them I think upwards of six months replacing a very old PHP application with what time was
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.03,0:26:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Blot当时被认为是相当现代的JS框架\Nconsidered a very modern JavaScript application but at the same time react
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.27,0:26:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,但是与此同时Blot的竞争对手React也开始被用于Facebook的生产项目，而且组建了团队\Nwas also now actually deployed for real on Facebook and had a team that was forming around it
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.68,0:27:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,所以现状变成了Facebook内部有两个前端开发框架并存，两个框架解决同一类问题且都有生产应用\Nso we now had two viable Frameworks that were both live on Facebook both solving real problems
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.08,0:27:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,, 这是不应该的，特别是两个框架的代码相似到会让人分不清哪个是哪个\Nwe shouldn't have two especially two that were similar similar enough to confuse people like if you looked at a code
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.65,0:27:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,并且对比两个框架的代码会发现，虽然代码差不多但是它们的工作原理非常不同\Ntheir code almost looked identical but that worked really differently it would
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.38,0:27:23.01,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你需要同时和两个框架打交道，这种情况简直是噩梦，所以我们需要决定谁去谁留\Nactually be an absolute nightmare if you had to work in both so we had to decide which which to use
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.01,0:27:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,[Music]
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.29,0:27:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,最终我(Bolt负责人)和Jordan(React创造者)做了一个长长的讨论\Na lot of this was ended up being a conversation between myself and Jordan
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.00,0:27:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,我们做了很多枯燥的性能测试，尝试找到两个框架应用的边缘案例we did an evaluation of boredom a lot of performance-based stuff and trying to figure out where the edge cases were
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.90,0:27:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,React的优势显然在于它能很好地处理复杂性\Non the pro side of react obviously there's all the things that we know now it handles complexity way way more even
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.22,0:27:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,比如说在用Bolt重写"广告创建流"模块的时候，我们已经出现不得不写出意大利面条代码的情况\Nwhen writing the as creation flow in bold we had already hit one place that you just could not do in Bolt without writing spaghetti code and you can do in
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.62,0:28:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,但是使用React可以很好解决这个问题，我们认为尽管这种情况可能只会在十个项目中出现一次\Nreact so we knew in the future even if it was only 10 of the experiences we were building we're going to run into this problem again now it might only be
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.72,0:28:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,但是当你放大到整个公司，其缺陷也会急速放大\N10 unmaintainable but as you scale that across a company that is growing rapidly this becomes an absolute mess
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.96,0:28:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,, React的缺点是它还没有经过足够多的考验，很多东西当时React根本做不到\Nthe cons of it on the other hand were that react in a lot of ways was not battle tested yet there's a lot of things that simply
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.53,0:28:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,比如它不能很好处理表单，文本框\Ndidn't work in react it couldn't handle forms they'd never done a text box and
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.44,0:28:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,处理表单元素比如单选按钮时过于复杂，还有就是会不必要地重新渲染大块UI而导致性能问题\Nthere's a lot of complexities around handing awkward form controls like radio buttons and so on that it messed up just performance issues where it would try and re-render large blocks
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.52,0:28:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,也就是他们还没来得及做Raact框架的性能优化\Nso they hadn't had to do all of the performance improvements that obviously exist now
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.12,0:28:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,, 从组织管理角度，另一个对React不利的情况是我们刚刚花了六个月用Bolt重写了业务\Non the organizational side that the other con was that we had just done the six-month rewrite in both
